It develops a perfectly normal chick.
But then the problem begins.
"The problem is that the chick needs to find a hold; it needs to be able to stand on its legs and start moving," explains the head of the Institute of Medical-Biological Problems RAN, Vladimir Sychew.
Without solid ground, the chicks wildly overwhelm themselves.
Ten hours later, the instincts of the newborns completely mutilated.
The chicks did not respond to light and noise.
Four days later, they simply died.
"Two times we let chicks slip and then put the whole thing in place, because it's simply impossible to work with them there," said Vladimir Sychew, who was involved in the failed experiment with the chicks in space.
The last cage with animals flew into orbit 16 years ago.
The experiments will continue in the spring of 2013.
However, only same-sex species will be found on the biosatellite "Bion".
There was an experiment with rats that were already fertilized into space.
In principle, nothing special was found.
