What are the main sexually transmitted diseases?
Bacterial STIs include syphilis, chlamydia and tripper (gonorrhea).
Common viral STIs are HIV, human papillomaviruses, genital herpes or hepatitis.
Felt lice and scabies belong to the parasitic STI.
Who are the main groups of people affected?
Syphilis and trippers are especially common in men who have sex with men.
The Robert Koch Institute estimates that at least four out of five syphilis cases reported in Germany are transmitted through sexual contacts between men.
In heterosexual adults, chlamydia infections, trichomonades, candidosis (fungus), tripper and human papillomaviruses are common sexually transmitted diseases.
